## F) Execution Model (No Look-ahead)
### Backtest execution
- Signals computed at close of day t
- Trades filled at open of day t+1 with slippage/commission
- Apply slippage:
  - buy fill = open*(1 + SLIPPAGE_BPS/10000)
  - sell fill = open*(1 - SLIPPAGE_BPS/10000)

### Paper trading execution (live-ready)
- Run once per day ~10–15 minutes before close
- Use latest data to compute signal (be explicit whether using intraday proxy or yesterday’s close)
- Place orders as:
  - Prefer **MOC** if broker supports (or limit near close with safety buffer)
- Include safeguards:
  - if data stale → do nothing + alert
  - if order rejected → retry with backoff
  - if position mismatch → reconcile and alert
  - kill-switch checks before sending orders

