## K) Overfitting Audit (MANDATORY REPORT)
Generate an “Overfit Audit” section with these checks:

### 1) Parameter Stability
- Show selected params across folds
- Flag if parameters vary wildly (instability = overfit risk)

### 2) Sensitivity / Robustness
- For best params, perturb:
  - MA windows ±10% (e.g., 45/225, 55/275)
  - VOL_LOOKBACK ±20
  - VOL_TARGET ±0.05
- Confirm performance doesn’t collapse

### 3) Regime Dependence
- Segment OOS performance by:
  - Bull regime days vs bear regime days vs sideways (define sideways as frequent flips / low MA spread)
- Show which regime drives returns

### 4) Cost/Slippage Stress
- Re-run OOS with slippage = {0, 5, 15} bps
- Show how fragile returns are to costs

### 5) Data Leakage Checks
- Assert:
  - signals never use future bars
  - execution uses t+1 open
  - training parameter selection never touches test window

### 6) Reality Checks
- Compare OOS vs buy-and-hold QQQ and buy-and-hold TQQQ (same time period)
- Report if outperformance is concentrated in a single year (warning)

The audit should output:
- A short risk rating: {Low, Medium, High} overfit risk
- Bullet list explaining why

